'''''Fear Thy Neighbor''''' is an [[Action fiction|action]] [[Horror (genre)|horror]] [[Thriller (genre)|thriller]] [[true crime]] [[television documentary|documentary]]/[[Drama (film and television)|drama]] television series which premiered on April 14, 2014, on the [[Investigation Discovery]] channel.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/tvshows/fear-thy-neighbor/551470/|title=''Fear Thy Neighbor'' – TV Show|work=[[TV Guide]]|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|accessdate=August 31, 2015}}</ref> The show focuses on various feuds between neighbors which usually escalate into tragedies.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=August 31, 2015|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2014/04/16/investigation-discovery-unveils-new-programming-slate-including-the-perfect-murder-cell-block-psychic/254680/|title=Investigation Discovery Unveils New Programming Slate Including 'The Perfect Murder' & 'Cell Block Psychic'|first=Sara|last=Bibel|work=[[TV by the Numbers]]|publisher=[[Tribune Digital Ventures]]|date=April 16, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|accessdate=August 31, 2015|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2015/04/13/investigation-discovery-reveals-new-season-of-fear-thy-neighbor-premiering-monday-april-13-at-10-9c-493002/20150413id01/|title=Investigation Discovery Reveals New Season of "Fear Thy Neighbor," Premiering Monday, April 13 at 10/9c|work=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=May 13, 2015}}</ref> The narrator for the series is voice actor Tish Iceton.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=August 9, 2018|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm8043773/|title=Tish Iceton|work=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=May 13, 2016}}</ref>

The series is a international co-production between Canadian factual entertainment company [[Cream Productions]], American cable television network Investigation Discovery (and later its [[Investigation Discovery (Canada)|Canadian version]]) and French-language Canadian documentary television channel [[Canal D]] (production position later taken over by its crime-focused spinoff [[Investigation (TV channel)|Canal D/Investigation]], later known as [[Investigation (TV channel)|Investigation]]), with [[Bell Media]], as owner of Canal D, Investigation and Investigation Discovery Canada, producing the series for its three specialty channels via its original programming production unit.

