{{Infobox comics creator | name = Philip Tan | image = | image_size = | caption = Tan at the [[New York Comic Con]] in Manhattan, October 9, 2010. | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth year and age|1978}} | birth_place = [[Manila]], [[Philippines]] | death_place = | nationality = | cartoonist = | writer = | artist = | penciller = y | inker = y | editor = | publisher = | letterer = | colorist = | alias = | signature = <!-- very optional --> | notable works = ''[[Spawn (comics)|Spawn]]'' | awards = | website = }}
'''Philip Tan''' (born 1978) is a [[comic book writer/artist]] best known for his work on ''[[Spawn (comics)|Spawn]]'',<ref>[http://www.comicsbulletin.com/features/113255804146920.htm Philip Tan: The Spawning Ground], [[Comics Bulletin]], November 21, 2005</ref><ref>[http://www.spawn.com/features/spawn150/artists.04.html Spawn], Spawn Milestones</ref> ''[[Uncanny X-Men]]'' and ''[[Iron Man]]''.
==Career== Tan graduated at the [[University of Santo Tomas]] with a [[Bachelor of Architecture|Bachelor's Degree in Architecture]].{{fact|date=October 2013}}
Tan was the penciller of ''[[Final Crisis: Revelations]]''<ref>[http://forum.newsarama.com/showthread.php?t=153995 Philip Tan on Final Crisis: Revelations], [[Newsarama]], April 17, 2008</ref> as well as the "Agent Orange" ''[[Green Lantern]]'' story arc, which started in ''Green Lantern'' #39 and ran through issue 42.<ref>[http://www.newsarama.com/comics/120819-Philip-Tan-Orange.html Painting It Orange: Philip Tan on the Orange Lanterns], [[Newsarama]], December 19, 2008</ref><ref>[http://www.newsarama.com/comics/120818-OrangeLanterns.html FIRST LOOK: Orange Lanterns by Philip Tan], [[Newsarama]], December 21, 2008</ref><ref>[http://www.newsarama.com/comics/010915-OrangeLanterns.html Philip Tan: Three More Orange Lanterns], [[Newsarama]], January 15, 2009</ref>
Following Agent Orange he will be penciling the second three issue arc of Grant Morrison's [[Batman and Robin (comic book)|Batman and Robin series with issue 6 being his last.]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://comics.ign.com/articles/986/986031p3.html|title=Grant Morrison's New Batman and Robin|author=Dan Phillips}}</ref>
Tan has illustrated cards for the ''[[Magic: The Gathering]]'' collectible card game.
In 2011 Tan was the artist on ''[[Hawkman (comic book)|Hawkman]]'', which was part of [[DC Comics]]' company-wide title relaunch, [[The New 52]].<ref>[http://www.newsarama.com/comics/dcnu-philip-tan-savage-hawkman-111026.html Artist Philip Tan on the Changes to the DCnU Hawkman][[Newsarama]], 26 October 2011</ref>
In 2016, Philip Tan worked on the new Suicide Squad Rebirth series co-drawing with Jim Lee. <ref>http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/suicide-squad-rebirth-creators-new-916202</ref>
