{{Infobox play | name = The House of Love | image = | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = | writer = | chorus = | characters = {{plainlist| *[[Jayne Mansfield]] *[[Mickey Hargitay]] }} | mute = {{plainlist| }} | setting = | premiere = {{Start date|1960|12|29}} 12.29.60 | place = [[Tropicana Las Vegas]] | orig_lang = | subject = | genre = [[Striptease]] [[revue]] | web = }}
'''''The House of Love''''' is a [[striptease]] [[revue]] starring [[Jayne Mansfield]]. In December 1960, [[Dunes (hotel and casino)|Dunes hotel and casino]] launched Mansfield's revue ''The House of Love'' (produced by Jack Cole, co-starring Hargitay). She received $35,000.00 a week as her salary (${{formatnum:{{Inflation|US|35000|1960}}}} in {{Inflation-year|US}} dollars{{inflation-fn|US}}), which was the highest in her career.<ref>{{harvnb|Strait|1992|p=110}}</ref><ref>{{harvnb|Faris|1994|p=24}}</ref> Her wardrobe for the shows featured a gold mesh dress with sequins to cover her nipples and pubic region.<ref name=cultvegas>Mike Weatherford, ''Cult Vegas: The Weirdest! The Wildest! The Swingin'est Town on Earth!'', pages 230-232, Huntington Press Inc, 2001, {{ISBN|9780929712710}}</ref><ref name=burbank>Jeff Burbank, ''Las Vegas Babylon'', pages 113-114, Franz Steiner Verlag, 2007, {{ISBN|9781861059666}}</ref><ref>{{harvnb|Faris|1994|p=46}}</ref> That controversial sheer dress that was referred to as "Jayne Mansfiled and a few sequins".<ref>{{harvnb|Strait|1992|p=94}}</ref>
